<% content_for :title, "Getting Started — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Getting Started", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Getting Started</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">New to Small City? Here's how to create an account and book your first session.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">1. Create an Account</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Click <strong>Sign Up</strong> in the top navigation to create your account.
            Enter your email address and choose a password of at least 12 characters.
            You can optionally add your name as well.
          </p>
          <p>
            After submitting the form you'll be taken to the sign-in page. Check your inbox for a
            verification email from Small City Studio — you'll need to click the link in that email
            before you can book.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">2. Verify Your Email</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Open the verification email and click <strong>Verify my email</strong>. You'll be signed
            in automatically and taken to the home page. Email verification is required once before
            you can hold or pay for studio time.
          </p>
          <p>
            The link expires after 24 hours. If it has expired, sign in and use the
            <strong>Resend verification email</strong> link shown in the yellow banner at the top of
            the page.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">3. Browse the Calendar</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            The home page shows available studio time for the next 30 days, grouped by date.
            Red slots are available to book. Click any red slot to start selecting your session time.
          </p>
          <p>
            See <strong><%= link_to "Booking Calendar", help_calendar_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %></strong>
            for a full explanation of slot colors and how to select multiple consecutive hours.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">4. Check Out and Pay</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            After selecting your slots, click <strong>Continue to Checkout</strong>. The app places a
            short hold on your time while you review and pay. Payment is handled securely through Stripe —
            your card details are never stored by the studio.
          </p>
          <p>
            See <strong><%= link_to "Checkout & Payment", help_checkout_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %></strong>
            for details on the hold timer and the payment flow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">5. Your Booking is Confirmed</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            After successful payment you'll be redirected to a confirmation page. Your booking
            appears under <strong>My Bookings</strong> in the top navigation.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you have push notifications enabled, you'll also receive a notification confirming
            the date and time. See <strong><%= link_to "Notifications", help_notifications_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %></strong>
            to learn how to enable them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
